# Course 2: Ask Questions to Make Data-Driven Decisions

## Summary

This course focused on developing the ability to ask effective, SMART questions (Specific, Measurable, Action-oriented, Relevant, Time-bound) to guide data analysis. It also introduced the process of problem-solving in analytics and the development of strong stakeholder communication.

### Key Topics:
- Creating effective problem statements
- Formulating SMART questions
- Stakeholder communication and documentation
- Introduction to the scope of work (SOW) and data bias

### Skills Gained:
- Translating business problems into data questions
- Writing clear and actionable SOWs
- Practicing empathy and communication in data analytics
